          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "In this section, the Sleuth reviews the case in an attempt to find where they went wrong. In reviewing the crime's chain of events, the Sleuth identifies a seemingly inconsequential piece of evidence from Act 1, which has been overlooked until information revealed in Act 3 shows it to be crucial. This new understanding makes the Sleuth (and keen reader) aware of the error ahead of the other characters."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Give an overview of the case and chain of events. What was the critical piece of evidence overlooked in Act 1?"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Why was the crucial evidence overlooked, and what new information offered in Act 3 illuminated its importance?"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Allow the keen reader to piece together the error ahead of the other characters – this increases reader buy-in and connection to the story."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Consider how this section develops the subplot."
